<subSubSection box="[136,576,1472,1499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,576,1472,1499]" box="[136,576,1472,1499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<heading bold="true" box="[136,576,1472,1499]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,576,1472,1499]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
Key to 
<taxonomicName authority="von Linne (1753: 969)" authorityName="von Linne" authorityPageNumber="969" authorityYear="1753" box="[222,345,1472,1499]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[222,345,1472,1499]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">Callitriche</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in 
<collectingCountry box="[471,576,1472,1498]" name="Morocco" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">Morocco</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" type="key">
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1540,1562]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1540,1562]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">1. Fruit unwinged, outer edge of mericarps rounded..............................................................................................................................2</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1569,1591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1569,1591]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">- Fruit with an obvious wing.................................................................................................................................................................3</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1598,1620]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1598,1620]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
2. Pollen and therefore anthers yellow; leaves connate, at least apical leaves with more than one vein ....................6. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Le Gall" authorityYear="1852" box="[1300,1451,1598,1620]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusangula">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1300,1451,1598,1620]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. obtusangula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
- Pollen translucent, anthers colourless sometimes appearing whitish; leaves not connate, no leaves with more than one vein .......... .....................................................................................................................................................9a. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1986" baseAuthorityName="Rouy" baseAuthorityYear="1910" box="[1145,1450,1655,1677]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="truncata" subSpecies="occidentalis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1145,1450,1655,1677]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1145,1257,1656,1677]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. truncata</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1333,1450,1655,1677]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">occidentalis</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1684,1706]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1684,1706]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">3. Pollen translucent, anthers colourless and typically very difficult to locate ......................................................................................4</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1713,1735]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1713,1735]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">- Pollen and therefore anthers yellow, anthers usually obvious............................................................................................................7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
4. Leaves connate; styles reflexed with remains ultimately appressed to groove between mericarps of fruit; fruiting pedicel ≤ 
<quantity box="[1378,1447,1742,1764]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="12.0">12 mm</quantity>
; at least some upper leaves usually with more than one vein..............................................................................................................5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1800,1822]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1800,1822]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
- Leaves not connate; styles erect or spreading; fruiting pedicel ≤ 
<quantity box="[826,884,1800,1821]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
; all leaves with only one vein ............................................6
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1828,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1828,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
5. Fruit ± isodiametric; wing narrow, with smooth margin.......................................................................... 1a. 
<taxonomicName box="[1226,1451,1828,1850]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="brutia" subSpecies="brutia">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1226,1451,1828,1850]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1226,1314,1828,1850]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. brutia</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1391,1451,1828,1850]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">brutia</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1450,1857,1879]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1450,1857,1879]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
- Fruit wider than long; wing broad, with irregular margin.................................................................. 1b. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Prancl" baseAuthorityName="Warburg &amp; Eig" baseAuthorityYear="1929" box="[1189,1450,1857,1879]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="brutia" subSpecies="naftolskyi">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1189,1450,1857,1879]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1189,1277,1857,1879]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. brutia</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1353,1450,1857,1879]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">naftolskyi</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1450,1886,1908]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1450,1886,1908]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
6. Wing of fruit broad, as wide as ovule or nearly so......................................................................................................4. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1961" box="[1325,1450,1886,1908]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lusitanica">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1325,1450,1886,1908]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. lusitanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1915,1937]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1915,1937]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
- Wing of fruit very narrow, appearing as a rim around the mericarps............................................... 9b. 
<taxonomicName box="[1178,1451,1915,1936]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="truncata" subSpecies="truncata">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1178,1451,1915,1936]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1178,1290,1915,1936]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. truncata</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1367,1451,1915,1936]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">truncata</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1944,1966]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1944,1966]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">7. Mature fruit blackish ..........................................................................................................................................................................8</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" box="[136,1451,1972,1994]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,1972,1994]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">- Mature fruit brownish or grey-brown.................................................................................................................................................9</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
8. Fruit distinctly wider than long; filaments &lt;
<quantity box="[639,715,2001,2023]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.2 mm</quantity>
, anthers typically low in leaf axils and difficult to locate; plants monoecious with most leaf axils containing both 
<specimenCount box="[561,579,2031,2052]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
and 
<specimenCount box="[626,644,2031,2052]" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
flowers.................................................................................................... 3. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Braun ex Hegelmaier" authorityYear="1864" box="[1351,1451,2030,2052]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="deflexa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1351,1451,2030,2052]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">C. deflexa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[136,1452,1540,2081]" lastBlockId="15.[136,1451,159,296]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
<keyLead lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="68" pageId="14" pageNumber="67">
- Fruit ± isodiametric or slightly longer than wide; filaments erect &lt;
<quantity box="[880,955,2059,2081]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="14" pageNumber="67" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.5 mm</quantity>
and anthers typically held clear above floating or terrestrial leaves; plants dioecious or predominantly of one gender, flowers solitary .................................................. 5. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1976" box="[1339,1451,159,181]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mathezii">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1339,1451,159,181]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">C. mathezii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,159,296]" box="[136,1451,187,210]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,187,210]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
9. Fruit &lt;
<quantity box="[283,356,188,209]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
wide, wider than long on pedicel ≤ 
<quantity box="[702,769,188,210]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="55.0">55 mm</quantity>
......................................................................................7. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1973" box="[1312,1451,187,209]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regis-jubae">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1312,1451,187,209]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">C. regis-jubae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,159,296]" box="[136,1451,217,239]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,217,239]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
- Fruit ≥ 
<quantity box="[283,356,217,238]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" unit="mm" value="1.4">1.4 mm</quantity>
diameter, ± isodiametric, ± sessile ..........................................................................................................................10
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,159,296]" box="[136,1450,245,267]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[136,1450,245,267]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
10. Testa cribrose; larger leaves with ≤ 17 parallel veins.................................................................................................... 2. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schotsman" authorityYear="1965" box="[1341,1450,245,267]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="cribrosa">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1341,1450,245,267]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">C. cribrosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="15.[136,1451,159,296]" box="[136,1451,274,296]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
<keyLead box="[136,1451,274,296]" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">
- Testa in loops; largest leaves with no more than seven parallel veins ......................................................................... 8. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[1335,1451,274,296]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Plantaginaceae" genus="Callitriche" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="15" pageNumber="68" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stagnalis">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1335,1451,274,296]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="68">C. stagnalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
